title.narrative: STRENGTHENED NATIONAL SYSTEMS TO DELIVER NUTRITION- SPECIFIC INTERVENTIONS

description.narrative: Strengthened national systems to deliver at scale improved and quality nutrition- specific interventions, which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition (Covid), Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition In Early Childhood (Covid), Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children under 5, pregnant and lactating women, and adolescents have access to and utilize quality and effective nutrition services, and adopt improved nutrition practices

title.narrative: Strengthened national systems to deliver at scale improved and quality nutrition- specific interventions

description.narrative: UNICEF continued supporting nutrition-specific interventions focusing on continued essential nutrition services in context of COVID-19. The growth monitoring and promotion coverage was maintained at 86 per cent, covering most of under-five children. Vitamin A supplementation and deworming tablets were provided to 152,931 children aged 6-11 months and 1,334,148 children aged 12-59 months. Severe acute malnutrition programme (SAM) treatment reached 5,643 children, of whom 94 per cent were cured. Adolescent nutrition booklet in Kinyarwanda provided nutrition and anemia prevention messages for in and out of school adolescents. National community health workers curriculum was finalized including comprehensive nutrition modules and training package. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2021
